-lrb- cnn -rrb- on the eve of the one-year mark since nearly 300 schoolgirls were abducted by boko haram in nigeria , malala yousafzai released an `` open letter '' to the girls monday .
`` like you , i was a target of militants who did not want girls to go to school , '' she writes in the letter .
the 17-year-old nobel peace prize winner survived an attack by the taliban , which had singled her out for blogging from pakistan about the importance of staying in school .
in the letter , she calls on the nigerian government and the international community to do more to rescue the girls .